Set up a KVM hypervisor

x86 hardware with virtualization extensions:

1. Intel VT
-if you are buying the hardware to run KVM on:

Visit the product specification site (ark.intel.com). Enter the number of the processor in the search box located on the right side. In 
the processor product page, and under Advanced Technologies, check to see if Intel® Virtualization Technology (VT-x) is supported.

EX) Intel Core i5-9400F 2.9 GHz 6-Core Processor
https://ark.intel.com/content/www/us/en/ark/products/190883/intel-core-i5-9400f-processor-9m-cache-up-to-4-10-ghz.html
***Intel® Virtualization Technology (VT-x) ‡ Yes ***

-if you already have the hardware, check to see if your processor supports it on your Linux OS that's going to run the KVM:

# grep -e 'vmx' /proc/cpuinfo		#Intel systems


2. AMD-V

# grep -e 'svm' /proc/cpuinfo		#AMD systems


*In addition, you can confirm the KVM modules are loaded in the kernel:

# lsmod | grep kvm




https://www.tecmint.com/install-kvm-in-centos-8/

